---

🧠 What are Cookies?

**Cookies** are small pieces of data stored in the **user’s browser**.

👉 Used to:

* Store user info
* Track sessions
* Save preferences

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Cookie Flow

```text id="k2m8p4"
Server → Sends Cookie → Browser Stores → Sends back with request
```

---

🔷 Example Cookie

```javascript id="m4p8k2"
res.cookie("username", "Saakshi");
```

---

🔷 Read Cookie

```javascript id="p2k9m4"
req.cookies.username;
```

---

🔷 Install Cookie Parser

```bash id="t8k2p4"
npm install cookie-parser
```

Use:

```javascript id="u4k9p2"
const cookieParser = require("cookie-parser");
app.use(cookieParser());
```

---

🔷 What are Sessions?

**Sessions** store user data on the **server**, not browser.

👉 Browser stores only **session ID**

---

🔷 Session Flow

```text id="v2k8p4"
Client → Login → Server creates session → Sends session ID
        ↓
Client sends session ID with each request
        ↓
Server verifies session
```

---

🔷 Install Session Middleware

```bash id="w8k2p4"
npm install express-session
```

---

🔷 Setup Session

```javascript id="x4k9p2"
const session = require("express-session");

app.use(session({
  secret: "secretKey",
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: true
}));
```

---

🔷 Store Data in Session

```javascript id="y2k8p4"
app.get("/login", (req, res) => {
  req.session.user = "Saakshi";
  res.send("Logged in");
});
```

---

🔷 Access Session Data

```javascript id="z4k9p2"
app.get("/profile", (req, res) => {
  res.send(req.session.user);
});
```

---

🔷 Destroy Session

```javascript id="a2k8p4"
req.session.destroy();
```

---

🔷 Cookies vs Sessions

| Feature    | Cookies     | Sessions        |
| ---------- | ----------- | --------------- |
| Storage    | Browser     | Server          |
| Security   | Less secure | More secure     |
| Size limit | Small       | Large           |
| Speed      | Faster      | Slightly slower |

---

🔷 Cookie Options

```javascript id="b4k9p2"
res.cookie("user", "Saakshi", {
  maxAge: 1000 * 60 * 60,
  httpOnly: true
});
```

✔ `httpOnly` → secure
✔ `maxAge` → expiry

---

🔷 Secure Cookies

```javascript id="c2k8p4"
res.cookie("token", "abc123", {
  secure: true
});
```

✔ Works with HTTPS

---

🔷 Session Middleware Options

```javascript id="d4k9p2"
app.use(session({
  secret: "secretKey",
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  cookie: { maxAge: 60000 }
}));
```

---

🔷 Real-World Authentication Flow

```text id="e2k8p4"
User Login
   ↓
Server creates session
   ↓
Session ID stored in cookie
   ↓
User requests protected route
   ↓
Server verifies session
```

---

🔷 Cookies + Sessions Together

✔ Cookie stores session ID
✔ Session stores user data

---

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ Storing sensitive data in cookies
❌ Not setting expiry
❌ Not securing cookies
❌ Not destroying sessions

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💡 Best Practices

✔ Use httpOnly cookies
✔ Use secure cookies (HTTPS)
✔ Use sessions for authentication
✔ Clear sessions on logout

